@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

GPLOT is a program for converting the ANSI/ISO standard Computer Graphics
Metafile format data to Postscript format.  Not as slim as MetaView (on aminet),
but MetaView doesn't do what I want  ie straight CGM->PS convert.

GPLOT supports binary, text and clear text format CGM files.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History"

Amiga compile version: a1
06 July 1996
    - compiled GPLOT source with amiga gcc2.7.2
        (Watch for compile errors in utils.c.
            reference to   out_info->name   should be  out_info->out_name
            seems to work.)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

    - compiled for 020

    - ixemul43+

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "Usage"

The full usage and documentation etc can be found on

    http://pscinfo.psc.edu/general/software/packages/gplot/gplot.html
and
    http://pscinfo.psc.edu/general/software/packages/cgm/cgm.html


Quick usage info:
    gplot -dps file.cgm >file.ps        Converts .cgm to .ps

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Problems" "Problems"

